After the patch.  It seems to SB's like thrust/pierce users pretty much get their cake and eat it too.  They have advantages to attacking Mid chain wearers and SB's, while SB's are now forced into taking advantages against other tanks, while losing our advantage over pierce/thrust assassins.<br>
<br>
Since SB's have always only been able to spec Slash, this is pretty much the role we all have taken from Day 1.  Personally, I have a Soulblade (I guess that is what it is dubbed now), that I use specifically to play bodyguard to our healing classes, archers, etc, against other assassins.  This is also why I chose Slash for my Inf, because I wanted to fill a similar role for Scouts/Casters.  With the new resists, I can respec my Inf to thrust, fill the same role without too much trouble and get advantages to chain wearers, while I have no idea what to do with my SB.<br>
